result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (4th w/in 5 yrs) was dismissed by the court.

  • Danielle R Cox was found guilty of OWI (4th w/in 5 yrs), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Danielle R Cox in court with Attorney Jonathan A. Lavoy.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Shannon Tenney appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  Count #2 is dismissed by operation of law.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Lavoy makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

4 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 2 days)
  -  2 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  2 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

*D/L REVOCATION:  30 months.
*IGNITION INTERLOCK:  30 months.

TERM OF PROBATION:  2 YEARS;   * May be transferred to Washington County*

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
*Not to operate a motor vehicle without a valid driver's license
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done 
*4 Months of Day Report Center consecutive to condition time (see below) 

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation - to be forward to Town of Brookfield Police Department);

FINE:  $1,819.00 & $250.00 DNA surcharge (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  8 MONTHS HUBER, Non-working hours with standard release conditions - LAST 4 MONTHS STAYED (NOTE:  Defendant is a school teacher but is still allowed huber privileges in the summer) to commence forthwith.  Defendant taken into custody.  May be transferred to Washington County. 

DAY REPORT CENTER:  4 MONTHS, Consecutive to Huber sentence.  Good time not allowed on DRC.  If defendant successfully completes Day Report Center, the 4 MONTHS of Huber stayed will be permanently stayed.
